    "managed by `capabilities`. Use `capabilities list` to inspect the installed "
    "set and project gate, and `capabilities help` for the manager contract. "
    "For an enabled capability, start with `<name> help`; use `<name> doctor` to "
    "prove readiness, `<name> connections` to inspect credential resolution, and "
    "`<name> guide` for its how-to guides. Project policy is controlled by "
    "`capabilities enable|disable`; do not change a gate without the user's "
    "instruction. Exit 4 is policy — a disabled capability or a read-only "
    "connection; ask the user, never lift a gate yourself."
)

